# Agent handover log maintenance

Whenever you complete a **user-requested** change to this repository or a substantive **action** that alters repo files, tooling, or layout (including config, dependencies, tests, CI, packaging), update `docs/ai-agent-handoff.md`:

1. Add a new log entry at the top of the existing **Log entries** section (keep **newest first**).
2. Include **date**, **trigger** (what was asked), **actions** (paths touched, key commands), **outcome**, and **follow-ups** if any remain.

Skip logging if the conversation was purely explanatory and nothing in the repo changed—unless the user explicitly asks to record it.

If `docs/ai-agent-handoff.md` is missing, recreate it with these headings in this order:
`# AI agent handoff`, `## Purpose`, and `## Log entries`. Under `## Log entries`, prepend the
newest entry first and include **date**, **trigger**, **actions**, **outcome**, and **follow-ups**
if any remain.
